{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/palliative-care-constipation/background-information/causes/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"0ea3e359-97ed-57ae-9e85-9efea8886a68","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e49c0f54-fd03-4530-87e7-45171f496144 --><h2>What are the common causes?</h2><!-- end field e49c0f54-fd03-4530-87e7-45171f496144 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f4ada8ca-bc76-4a60-94ff-aed1e3d019be --><!-- begin field 7dc21a92-5638-4735-9831-335866ccdde5 --><ul><li>Opioid analgesics are a common cause of constipation in people receiving palliative care [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/palliative-care-constipation/references/\">Fallon and O'Neill, 1998</a>]</li><li>However, the presence of <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/palliative-care-constipation/background-information/causes/#contributing-factors\">contributing factors</a> may exacerbate constipation in people receiving palliative care. </li></ul><!-- end field 7dc21a92-5638-4735-9831-335866ccdde5 --><!-- end item f4ada8ca-bc76-4a60-94ff-aed1e3d019be -->","topic":{"id":"4a368333-0a3d-5f76-906b-e2268205df04","topicId":"5f5e551e-9e71-40c0-a276-1d902ad4a4c1","topicName":"Palliative care - constipation","slug":"palliative-care-constipation","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2016","chapters":[{"id":"0bd21138-1475-5387-a62f-abf3cd882967","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"46765bba-ab36-575c-9b95-19157184302c","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"49b7dbfb-d2a6-52ac-a7b1-078151eb649e","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"8b3a00ff-7217-5c77-8f1f-b92183f39816","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"3e25df9e-81df-595b-99a9-ed6b07a209